What is Moochies?

Moochies is a fast-growing, end to end, telecommunications company, which includes a high margin subscription revenue stream. They deliver mobile phone products to a currently underserved market segment- namely young children under the age of 12.

Mobile phones are THE modern consumer product. They drive the revenues of the most valuable tech companies in the world and the penetration of telecommunications technology into our lives continues to broaden and grow. Moochies is positioned to be the breakout consumer brand for young kids over the next five years.

Moochies has full ownership and control of a globally market leading product, a proven team delivering record growth year on year, diverse and secure revenue streams and an aggressive features and distribution plan.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Problem and Market

Parents have problems giving adult mobile phones to young children, even though there is increasing pressure from this age range to have access to telecommunication solutions.

Adult mobile phones have no real age controls for apps; parents are unable to track what their kids are doing on traditional mobile phones; they worry about social media and the effect it has; who is contacting their children and why; as well as more mundane issues like will they break or lose an expensive phone.

Moochies provides the solution to all these concerns. Their phones look like watches but have an embedded sim card and are therefore standalone devices the same as a handset mobile phone, while at the same time being much harder to break or lose.

In addition, the Moochies proprietary firmware has parental control and supervision built in from the ground up. A parent can control exactly who can contact their child and have as much or as little control over their child's mobile phone as they wish. Additionally, there are several modes that the watch can be programmed to include Class Mode, to ensure the full focus and attention of children while at school.

The Market Opportunity

Kids' mobile phone usage has steadily increased, but for children under 12-years old, there is still a massive worldwide opportunity to provide the right product that parents are happy to buy before they move them onto an adult mobile phone. Moochies users start at 6 and the average age of a user is 9 years old.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value: Moochies currently operates in Australia, New Zealand, the UK, the USA and the Netherlands, and with over 4 million children in Australia alone under 14 years, there are 100,000s of new potential customers coming into their target age range every year, which doesn’t consider the USA with its addressable market in the tens of millions of subscribers.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Moochies Solution

So, what does Moochies do?

Moochies makes products that kids and parents want to buy. They offer an end-to-end solution, with full control over hardware and software, production, logistics, distribution and customer acquisition, service and billing.

Moochies develops, designs and manufactures phone watches, including firmware and launcher software.

They develop the Moochies app which goes on the parent's phone, giving them control of everything their child's watch does, and they develop the server and back-end solution that connects these two things together, as well as a telco billing platform that enables Moochies to take a monthly subscription from every active consumer.

Their phone watches deliver not just the things you would expect like calling, messaging and built-in tracking, but also video calling, the ability to take pictures and share them, safety and alert features, do not use and disturb features, safe and controllable contact lists, and they also have a huge variety of swappable straps and are water-resistant.

Moochies takes another leap forward in 2022 with built-in banking, meaning kids can now pay in the real world using their Moochies, the addition of full fitness and health features like you would find on Fitbit, and music streaming, enabling kids to listen to their favourite songs. With all of this again under the control and supervision of parents.

componentInstanceProperties.value:
Competitive Advantage

  • Moochies is an end to end solution, a unique feature compared to all competitors. With full control over hardware and software, production, logistics, distribution and customer acquisition, service and billing.
  • Moochies has at its core a high margin subscription revenue unlike anything else among the competition. This delivers long term monthly large volume revenue at a high margin in all territories from all active customers.
  • Moochies is aggressively priced to make purchases as easy as possible for consumers to drive volume and subscription revenue.
  • Moochies is unique in having global agreements with the world's largest distributor, Ingram Micro.
  • Moochies owns and develops all the technology it uses, increasing the value of the company and delivering a competitive advantage over the long term.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Growth Strategy

Moochies operates in five markets currently, including Australia, the UK, the USA, New Zealand and the Netherlands. They will be expanding this over 2022 into the EU, LATAM and APAC. Since being founded in 2015, Moochies has more than doubled its revenue every year, including during Covid, and 2022 is on track to be a record-breaking year yet again.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
The company is currently entering its most exciting year in its history, with the successful ranging in 2021 in 900 Best Buy stores, the USA’s largest electronics retailer, and they are now poised for a large-scale national retail rollout in multiple vendors across the USA.

Moochies now have more retailers in Australia than ever, with Big W, JB Hi Fi, Target, Office Works, Harvey Norman and more.

Moochies have national multi outlet distribution across New Zealand and the Netherlands, as well as new distribution rollouts agreed for the UK, Canada and Brazil, with more being agreed each month.

Moochies has three main revenue streams; high margin, low volume sales directly to consumers; low margin, high volume sales through distributors; and a high margin monthly recurring subscription revenue from every active user.

Recent results include:

  • Oct-Dec 2022 Revenue $5.25 Million- 60% increase YoY.
  • July-Dec 2022 Revenue $7.96 Million- 100% increase YoY.

Every sale they make earns Moochies high margin revenue over the long term.

componentInstanceProperties.name: richTextValue
componentInstanceProperties.value:
Exit Strategy

Moochies is strategically on target for an IPO listing on the ASX within the next 12 months.

The purpose of this round is to power forward revenues and position the company with higher volume international recurring subscription revenue. This will allow a successful and high float valuation.

The Offer

Moochies is raising a Convertible Note on the following terms:

  • The notes will be convertible but non-redeemable;
  • The interest rate will be 10% which will be capitalised through to conversion;
  • The notes will convert to equity at a 20% discount to the valuation negotiated at the next funding round.
  • 24-month Term
